abstract.label: Abstract
abstract.displayForm:
Video describing folio 52v


This set of papers documents some of Newton's early mathematical thinking, work that would develop into his theories of calculus. The texts include extracts he made from books he was reading and various notes and calculations - often on small scraps of paper he had to hand.

Transcriptions are available for parts of the papers, beginning on folio 48v.
